 SUNDAY DARE  Lere-Adams, the director of press in the sports ministry in a statement at the weekend disclosed that Dare, who visited the country’s contingent at their camp in Morocco, said that improved welfare would allow those representing the country in various tournaments to focus on national assignments. He said the Ministry of Youth and Sports Development would work with stakeholders, including the private sector to create the revolving fund. “Ensuring the sustenance and securing the commitment of our athletes will be largely dependent on their consistent welfare and provision of modern sports facilities. “To this end, the Ministry intends to create an Athletes Sustenance fund (ASF),” Dare said. The minister also said he would examine reports and previous initiatives on a similar fund to come up with a revolving fund that would best serve the athletes. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .